<H2>Brady Adds New 54" Printer to Full Line ColorPix Family of Large Format Printers </H2>

<P>MILWAUKEE, Wis.-- The Graphic Solutions Division of W.H. Brady has recently announced the introduction of the ColorPix&#153; Pro 54 Large Format Production System-- a new addition to the full line of large format printers offered by Brady. Like other printers in the ColorPix family, ColorPix&#153;&nbsp; Pro 54 combines Fujifilm technology with Brady's material expertise to bring you speed, width, variable resolution and durability all in one powerful printer.

<BR><BR>

The ColorPix&#153; Pro 54 System is ultra fast and, unlike competitive printers, offers variable widths up to 54&quot; and various resolutions capabilities up to 320 dpi. A true production system, ColorPix Pro 54 features oversized ink reservoirs and media supply rolls that allow users to perform large, unsupervised print runs. A new piezo electric print head allows for printing with pigmented inks to create outdoor applications where water fastness and UV durability are important. It also uses traditional dye-based inks for indoor applications. 

<BR><BR>

&quot;The ColorPix Pro&#153; 54 System really gives our customers options. It gives them the flexibility to select the width and resolution most appropriate for each specific application,&quot; said Pat Hay, Business Unit Manager for Brady's Graphic Solutions Division. &quot;And it gives them the speed they need to stay productive and profitable.&quot; 

<BR><BR>

The new ColorPix&#153; Pro 54 System also features a unique IJSS self-maintenance technology which continuously monitors the condition of the piezo print head and automatically enters into a self-cleaning mode when needed to assure the best possible output. 

<BR><BR>

As with other ColorPix&#153; series printers, the ColorPix Pro 54 utilizes Fujifilm's true 100% pigmented outdoor quality inks that are specially formulated to work with a wide variety of materials including BradyJet outdoor vinyl. Both the inks and the outdoor vinyl are guaranteed UV-resistant and water resistant for up to two years.

<BR><BR>

W.H. Brady Co. is an international provider of industrial identification and safety solutions. It markets more than 30,000 products including high-performance labels for circuit boards, industrial printing systems, data collection systems, software, signs, wide-format printing systems and various die-cut products serving a wide range of markets. Head quartered in Milwaukee, Wis., also has operations in Canada, Korea, Sweden, England, Belgium, France, Germany, Italy, Taiwan, Malaysia, Japan, Singapore, Hong Kong, Australia, New Zealand, and Brazil.

<BR><BR>


<P><BR>
